Per Capita City

Fatality rates can be compared between cities by standardizing all fatalities according to city populations, yielding the per capita rate.

Per Capita Metro

It is a common pattern for people to commute to cities during the workday even though they do not live in the city Therefore, I have decided to use the Metro area because I believe this will be a better indicator of road use. Larger metro areas will generate more trips, so it will be a metter proxy for actual traffic.
